quest.name: Raised on the Fallen
journal:
 Quest Sync
N'nagali is looking at you with motherly concern.
objectives: Deliver the rotting logs to N'nagali.

dialogue.name: NNAGALI
dialogue.text: MadameSir, if you could hold out your hand? I have something you really must eat. Please, I insist!

dialogue.name: NNAGALI
dialogue.text: Is that not the juiciest, sweetest, most invigorating thing you've ever tasted? I just finished baking a batch, and judging by your somewhat wan complexion, I thought you could use a little treat!

dialogue.name: NNAGALI
dialogue.text: Oh, don't worry─I know exactly what I'm feeding you. Though I've settled here in this haven of archived cultural treasures, I was once a student of the nutritional sciences at the Faculty of Medicine.

dialogue.name: NNAGALI
dialogue.text: The knowledge from that course certainly comes in useful when it comes to keeping my weary colleagues healthy and hale. ...Although I do struggle to find the time to collect all the ingredients I need.

dialogue.name: NNAGALI
dialogue.text: In fact, I wonder if you'd be willing to help in that regard? I was about to head out and gather some things east of here, but if you could scour the area to the northwest for a couple of rotting logs, I'd be ever so grateful!

dialogue.name: NNAGALI
dialogue.text: Yes, rotting logs! They don't need to be massive, but I will need them intact!

dialogue.name: NNAGALI
dialogue.text: Yes! These should be riddled with the little darlings!

dialogue.name: NNAGALI
dialogue.text: Thank you, both from me, and on behalf of my sure-to-be-appreciative fellow archivists! After all, no dish has more nutritional value than one made with beetle larvae!
